  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>Environmental news in China has seen some real highs and lows of late, ranging from the opening of the Beijing-Shanghai high-speed rail to a severe oil spill.</p>

<p><b>Beijing-Shanghai High-Speed Rail a Sell-Out</b></p>

<p>Trains began running on the new high-speed line between Beijing and Shanghai on June 30. Formerly a trip that could take over 12 hours, <A href="http://www.ens-newswire.com/ens/jul2011/2011-07-04-01.html">the new trains can make the 820 mile journey in less than 5</a>. In contrast, a trip of equivalent distance from Washington, DC to Orlando by train takes over 16 hours.</p></div>
