  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../blog-posts/chinas-industrial-energy-audits-new-study-lawrence-berkeley">China&#039;s Industrial Energy Audits: New Study From Lawrence Berkeley</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>A team of researchers at Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory‚Äôs <a href="http://china.lbl.gov/">China Energy Group</a> recently released an in-depth study on China‚Äôs industrial energy auditing practices. Because <a href="industry">China‚Äôs industrial sector</a> accounts for roughly two thirds of China‚Äôs total energy consumption, industrial energy audits play a critical role in assessing the efficacy of China‚Äôs policies and progress in improving energy efficiency.</p></div>
